.TH CORTEX-MCP 1 "2026-04-23" "cortex-mcp 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cortex-mcp \- Command-line tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cortex-mcp
[
B-h
    R | 
        B--help
               R]
.br
.B cortex-mcp

ICOMMAND
        R [
           ISUBCOMMAND
                      R] [
                          IARGS
                               R...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cortex-mcp
.SH COMMANDS
Available commands:
.TP
.B list
List all MCP servers with status
.TP
.B list-docs
List MCP docs with activation status
.TP
.B status
Show active MCP docs
.TP
.B activate
Activate MCP doc(s) in CLAUDE.md
.TP
.B deactivate
Deactivate MCP doc(s) from CLAUDE.md
.TP
.B show
Show detailed server info
.TP
.B docs
Display server documentation
.TP
.B test
Test server configuration
.TP
.B diagnose
Diagnose all server issues
.TP
.B snippet
Generate config snippet
.TP
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help message and exit
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT
Override for context directory (set automatically by Claude Code when running plugin commands)
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.claude/
Default context directory containing agents, modes, rules, and other configuration
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cortex-mcp-tui (1),
.BR cortex-mcp-workflow (1)
